        <definition xml:id="def-function-multiple-variables">
            <title>Function of Multiple Variables</title>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    A <term>function of multiple variables</term> <m>z = f(x_1,x_2,...,x_n)</m> is a rule which maps the ordered pair <m><fillin characters="5" /></m> in a subset <m>D</m> of <m>\R^n</m> to a unique real number <m><fillin characters="5" /></m>. The set <m>D</m> is called the <m><fillin characters="5" /></m> of the function, and the <m><fillin characters="5" /></m> is the set of all real numbers <m>z</m> such that <m><fillin characters="5" /></m>
                </p>
            </statement>
        </definition>

